'''= The Global Digital Activism Data Set (GDADS) will be an attempt to understand how grassroots social, political, and economic change occurs in the digital age.'''

URL = http://www.meta-activism.org/data-set/

=Description=

"The project aims to quantitatively study digital activism as a global phenomenon by creating an open case study database under a Creative Commons license that will be accessible to scholars and activists around the world.  You can download a free copy of the list of cases we collected so far and learn more below. We are currently working on our Codebook. A first version of the Dataset will be available for download soon."


